			<blockquote>
			<font face=helvetica size=-1>
<font face=helvetica size=3><b>Saturday February 19, 2000</b></font>
			<hr align=LEFT size=1 width=500 color=#000080>
<!---------------news---------------->
<Br>
<font face=helvetica size=2 color=#000080><b>Level Design and Programming Jobs at EA</b> - 01:06:09</font>
<br><br><blockquote>
Wanting to work on a Q3A engine title with some of the best people in the universe? Check this out. 

<blockquote> 
Electronic Arts is now hiring Level Designers for our Q3A based James Bond project, The World is Not Enough. Ideal candidates should have strong 3D skills, a great sense of space and lighting, and the ability to create innovative and exciting single-player and multi-player experiences.
Expertise with the latest 3D technology is required (e.g., Quake III Arena, Unreal, Half Life, etc.), and knowledge of the QERadiant level editor is a major plus.  Must be able to work well in a team oriented environment, and meet time related deadlines.  Candidate must be a U.S.
citizen or possess appropriate work visa for employment in the United States.  Relocation to Redwood City, California is required.  Interested parties should submit resume and level samples to:
 <br><br>
Alex Mayberry<br>
Lead Level Designer<br>
<a href=http://www.ea.com>Electronic Arts</a><br>
<a href=mailto:amayberry@ea.com>amayberry@ea.com</a><br>
</blockquote>
Also, we have news of these positions being opened. 
<blockquote>
<b>Senior Engineer</b><br> 
Electronic Arts is searching for a talented, experienced and team-oriented individual to help us bring Bond to the PC. We are looking for someone to expand our engineering department and are actively searching for experienced game programmers for the position of Senior Engineer. 
<br><br>
Responsibilities:
<br><br><ul> 
<li>Lead PC development on a parallel PC/PSXII team.  
<li>Develop and maintain PC architecture aspects.
<li>Multiplayer and GameSpy technology and integration issues.
<li>Design and development of new multiplayer game types.
<li>Hardware configuration issues.</ul>
 
Requirements: 
<br><br><ul>
<li>Extensive programming experience in the gaming industry. 
<li>Ability to create and maintain an organized task schedule. 
<li>A driven, self-starter who enjoys the commitment and rewards of creating cutting-edge technology. 
<li>Avid game player with an open mind and an understanding of games and gamers in general.
<li>Excellent communications and team skills.</ul>

We would like candidates to have five or more years of experience
programming for the gaming industry and to have a degree in Computer Science. Extensive experience developing and maintaining 3D graphics technology, multiplayer, and network code within engines such as Quake or Unreal, is highly preferred. 
<br><br> 
<b>Software Engineer</b> <br>
Electronic Arts is searching for a talented, experienced and team-oriented individual to help us bring Bond to the PC. We are looking for someone to expand our engineering department and are actively searching for experienced game programmers for the position of Software Engineer.
<br><br> 
Responsibilities:<br><ul>
<li>Code base development and integration of new code.
<li>User interface development
<li>FMV player integration
<li>Game performance tuning.
<li>Localization.
</ul>
Requirements: <br><ul>
<li>Significant programming experience in a team environment. <li>Driven, self-starting person that enjoys the commitment and rewards of creating interactive entertainment software.
<li>Avid game player with an open mind and an understanding of games and gamers in general.
<li>Excellent communications skills.  
</ul>
We would like candidates to have two or more years of experience programming for the gaming industry and to have a degree in Computer Science. Demonstrated experience developing and maintaining 3D graphics technology, such as Quake or Unreal, is highly preferred. 
 <br><br>
 
 
 
These are immediate openings.<br>  
Please send your resume to:<br>
 <br>
Greg Pisanich
Director of Development<br>
<a href=http://www.ea.com>Electronic Arts</a><br>
209 Redwood Shores Parkway<br>
Redwood City, CA 94065<br>
(650) 628-7391<br>
<a href=mailto:gpisanich@ea.com>gpisanich@ea.com</a></blockquote>
Sounds like a great thing! Spread the word these spots are gonna go fast!
<b><p align=right>Update by <a href="mailto:raygunn@gamedesign.net">raYGunn</a></p></b>
</blockquote>
<h3>Go <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net">back</a> to the main news page...</h3>
